  "name": "snowdb2_dotmod_nullsafe",
  "notes": "Primary differentiators: (1) dot wildcard char in LIKE (. instead of _), exercising the wildcard-char axis in a way distinct from firebird_click_wildcard's star; (2) MOD as a function-style operator rather than infix keyword or %; (3) null_safe_eq disabled entirely (no operator available), forcing ISNULL-pair workarounds; (4) bracket quoting + OFFSET/FETCH limit syntax from DB2/SQL Server lineage; (5) EXCEPT/INTERSECT tighter set-op precedence. The concat stays as || but with explicit string_concat_op semantic to test typed coercion paths.",
